text:
@bbarber_ @SamHartburn polar coords in @Geogebra:
Use a semicolon instead of a comma.
E.g. (1; pi/2) is point at radius 1, angle pi/2 (from positive x-axis).
Makes it MUCH easier to plot circular stuff.

text: #Calculus Ts: With @geogebra's RECTANGLESUM command, you can easily construct Riemann sums AND choose an (x_i*) for each interval [x_i, x_(i+1)]. Here, p = position of x_i* in each interval [x_i, x_(i+1)]. p = 0: left-endpoint. p = 0.5: midpoint, p = 1: right! #MTBoS #ITeachMath https://t.co/Ufp9BuxndV
